	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Slalom also requires proper handling of stack overflow, as I recently found out the hard way.  About 5 seconds into the title screen, it issues a JSR operation when the stack pointer register is 0, so half of the PC goes on the bottom of the stack and half goes on the top.  I was passing all of blargg's CPU test ROMs even with borked stack emulation so it was tricky to find, especially since I figured a Slalom glitch was probably going to be PPU-related.
<br />
<br />Sorry for the bump, but I wanted to tack this little bit of information onto the Slalom thread.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


